headline: United States Dog Food Forecast Report 2025: $28.81 Billion Market by 2033 Featuring ADM, General Mills, Heristo, Mars, Nestle, PLB, Schell & Kampeter, J. M. Smucker
summary: The United States dog food market is projected to reach USD 28.81 billion by 2033, growing from USD 20.90 billion in 2024 with a CAGR of 3.63% from 2025 to 2033. Key drivers include pet humanization and premiumization trends, reflecting the deep bond between pet owners and their dogs. The market's wide range of products, such as semi-moist options, wet canned food, and dry kibble, cater to diverse nutritional needs. The industry's growth is further supported by rising e-commerce and subscription
